    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This rod has a flanged head and the following properties.</p><p><em><strong>Alertness.</strong></em> While holding the rod, you have advantage on WIS (Perception) checks and on rolls for initiative.</p><p><em><strong>Spells.</strong></em> While holding the rod, you can use an action to cast one of the following spells from it: <em>@UUID[Compendium.black-flag.spells.Item.sJz2TidQi9dF5ClQ]{detect evil and good}</em>, <em>@UUID[Compendium.black-flag.spells.Item.jhMAM81keoyqBzsy]{detect magic}</em>, <em>@UUID[Compendium.black-flag.spells.Item.fJRDxf6O1Qd6vSZE]{detect poison and disease}</em>, or <em>@UUID[Compendium.black-flag.spells.Item.3MMJmBI63gipqU9b]{see invisibility}</em>.</p><p><em><strong>Protective Aura.</strong></em> As an action, you can plant the haft end of the rod in the ground, whereupon the rod’s head sheds bright light in a 60-foot radius and dim light for an additional 60 feet. While in that bright light, you and any creature that is friendly to you gain a +1 bonus to AC and saves and can sense the location of any invisible hostile creature that is also in the bright light.</p><p>The rod’s head stops glowing and the effect ends after 10 minutes, or when a creature uses an action to pull the rod from the ground. This property can’t be used again until the next dawn.</p>",
      "source": {
        "fallback": ""
      }
    },
